/**
 * @page Schedule Scheduled Defragmentation
 *
 * When some important files are frequently modifying
 * the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Task_Scheduler">Windows Task Scheduler</a>
 * can help to automate their defragmentation.
 * Set up scheduled tasks and you'll save a lot of your time.
 *
 * Examples of commands:
 * @par Defragment Firefox cache
 * @code
 * udefrag "%APPDATA%\Mozilla*"
 * @endcode
 *
 * @par Defragment Google Earth cache
 * @code
 * udefrag "%APPDATA%\Google\GoogleEarth*"
 * @endcode
 *
 * @par Defragment small files on all non-removable disks
 * @code
 * cmd.exe /C "set UD_SIZELIMIT=100M && udefrag --wait --all-fixed"
 * @endcode
 *
 * Visit <a href="http://ultradefrag.wikispaces.com/">ultradefrag.wikispaces.com</a> 
 * for tutorials and more examples.
